The examined specimens for this study were based on the collections housed at 
Incheon
National University and the 
Korea
National Arboretum. Additional moth samples were collected using two white screens (2.0m x 1.5m) illuminated by mercury vapor lamps (220 
V
/200W, Dongseong Co., 
Korea
) and four UV lamps (200W, Kumho, 
Korea
).The adult photographs were taken with a Dhyana 400DC camera (Tucsen Photonics, Fuzhou, 
China
) attached to the Leica S6D (Wetzlar, 
Germany
) stereomicroscope. The genital photographs were taken with a Dhyana 400DC camera (Tucsen Photonics, Fuzhou, 
China
) attached to the Leica S8AP0 stereo-microscope. All photographs were edited using Adobe Photoshop 2021. The dyeing used Mercury dibromofluorescein disodium salt and chlorazol black E (Sigma-Aldrich, 
USA
).

